<document> 

  <properties>
    <title>Map reads step</title>
    <author email="jourdren@biologie.ens.fr">Laurent Jourdren</author> 
  </properties> 



  <body>
  
    <section name="Map reads step">

      <p>This step allow to map reads with a mapper program.</p>  

      <ul>
	<li><b>Internal name</b>: mapreads</li> 
        <li><b>Available</b>: Both local and distributed mode</li>
        <li><b>Multithreaded in local mode</b>: Yes (mapper multithreading)</li>
        <li><b>Input</b>: filtered reads (e.g. <code>filtered_reads_1.fq</code>)</li>
        <li><b>Output</b>: alignments in SAM format (e.g. <code>mapper_results_1.sam</code>)</li>	
	<br/>
        <li><b>Optional parameters</b>:</li>
	<table>
                <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Default value</th></tr>
                <tr><td>mapper</td><td>string</td><td>The name of the mapper to use</td><td>None, this parameter is mandatory. (e.g. bowtie, bwa, soap)</td></tr>
                <tr><td>mapperArguments</td><td>string</td><td>Mapper additional command line arguments</td><td>See below in the next table</td></tr>
        </table>
        
	<br/>
        <li><b>Available built-in mappers</b>:</li>
	<table>
                <tr><th>Mapper name</th><th>Bundled version</th><th>Default mapper arguments</th></tr>
                <tr><td><a href="http://bowtie-bio.sourceforge.net/index.shtml">Bowtie</a></td><td>0.12.7</td><td>-k 10</td></tr>
                <tr><td><a href="http://bio-bwa.sourceforge.net/">BWA</a></td><td>0.5.8c</td><td>-l 28</td></tr>
                <tr><td><a href="http://soap.genomics.org.cn/soapaligner.html">SOAP2</a></td><td>2.20</td><td>-r 2 -l 28</td></tr>
        </table>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </body>
  
</document>
